		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>Hey Tim,</p>
<p>Good stuff. I know some doctors will prescribe antibiotics for the common cold!! How illiterate do you have to be to prescribe antibiotics for a viral infection? I have tried the whole supplement thing and can totally vouch for Vitamin C.</p>
<p>The trouble is people just don&#8217;t take enough of it!! And if your body is weak, as it is during a cold, you&#8217;re going to need more vitamin C. A good rule of thumb is to take enough C to saturate the body. Saturation is reached when you get diarrhea :)</p>
<p>Oh yeah and prepare for a lot of flatulence that day, so it&#8217;s wise to stay home. The last few time I&#8217;ve done this, I&#8217;ve gotten over the major symptoms of cold in no more than 48 hours. It has taken me up to 20-30 grams of vitamin C a day to get over it, and I&#8217;m usually normally functioning the next day.</p>
<p>The problem with things like OJ, is that to get the same effect from it you have to drink a LOT</p>
