				<a href="#comment-91663" alt="Permalink to this comment">11:58 am</a>
			</span>
			<br />
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ed1db9a46795c34bb92dc0abea7bb8cf?s=64&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-64 photo' height='64' width='64' />		</div>
		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>Followup to Rob Hinchcliffe&#8230;.I&#8217;ve been experimenting successfully with 1000mg of N-acetyl-L-cysteine (an acetylated amino acid) plus 500mg of Vit. C right before you start drinking booze and after the session is over.  The proposed mode of action is that these two together scavenge the acetaldehyde which is a by-product of alchohol breakdown &#8212; acetaldehyde the molecule that most people think is a major headache cause for hangovers.  You could also add half an ibuprofen tablet to the mix before you drink but beware if you have a sensitive stomach to NSAIDs (aspirin, ibuprofen, naproxen etc).  Avoid acetaminophen (tylenol) when drinking because it can amplify liver damage.</p>
					</div>
