			<br />
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/8b2d1bf0e27efa6113ccb3382c70ef57?s=64&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-64 photo' height='64' width='64' />		</div>
		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>As mentioned previously, a neti pot is the simplest and most comfortable way to perform sinus irrigation. Originated in India, a small ceramic pot has a long spout which is inserted in the nostril. The head is tilted to the opposite side, and a mild saline solution is flushed through the nose and expelled through the other nostril.</p>
<p>Try it. I guarantee you won&#8217;t go back to other messy means.</p>
					</div>
