<p>at initial onset of symptoms (sore throat, sinus congestion or hot forehead/headache) I do the following:</p>
<p>I will drink 64 ounces of water per day (you have to pee a ton but it is well worth it to boost your bodies ability to fight the cold)<br />
I will take 500 mg of vitamin C in the morning, lunch and dinner<br />
I will get sudafed daytiime 24 hour (the kind you have to sign for behind the counter)<br />
Menthol lozenges to sooth the throat and clear the sinus, as needed.</p>
